# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tableau Lens proxy — environment variables template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file (.env.example) is committed to git as documentation for what
# variables the proxy expects. Copy it to `.env` (which is gitignored) and
# fill in the real values.
#
# IMPORTANT: For deployed workers, these values must ALSO be set in
# Cloudflare's secret store using `wrangler secret put`. The .env file is
# only used for local development (via `wrangler dev`).
#
# To set a secret on the deployed worker:
#   wrangler secret put SERPER_API_KEY
#   (paste your key when prompted)
#
# To list what secrets are currently set on the worker:
#   wrangler secret list
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Serper.dev search API key (https://serper.dev/dashboard).
# Free tier: 2,500 queries/month, no credit card.
# Used by the worker to search for Tableau tutorials per chart type.
SERPER_API_KEY=your_serper_api_key_here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reference — these are NOT environment variables but worth documenting:
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Worker URL after `wrangler deploy`:
#   https://tableau-lens-proxy.<YOUR-CLOUDFLARE-SUBDOMAIN>.workers.dev
#
# KV namespace ID (also stored in wrangler.toml):
#   See `[[kv_namespaces]] id` in wrangler.toml
#
# Cloudflare account dashboard:
#   https://dash.cloudflare.com → Workers & Pages → tableau-lens-proxy
